<font color="#FF0000">REPLY TO TANKER</font><br>
<tt>Sat Jan  4 20:05:26 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Dear Tanker (N.A. Andreacchio),<br><br>
Happy holidays and best wishes for the New Year.We are a little wet out here, and some of us are keeping a close eye on the Sacramento River.... as it continues to rise... Sacramento Bee reported today that 100,000 people have been evacuated from our north-central Calilfornia area. Our wishes and hopes go out to these families.....<br><br>
Thank you for your response. We will have a very broad range of Vietnamese-American perspectives offered during the evening seminar: soldiers as well as civilians, evacuees as well as &quot;boat people,&quot; citizens who will relate their experiences, their joys as well as sorrows, and will address the ease-difficulty of social-cultural adjustment in America. Especially important will be the views of one speaker recently released from a &quot;re-education camp.&quot; <br><br>
Regarding the French era.... one speaker will consider the period from 1857 when French troops attacked Da Nang, through the Colonial period, World War II, post-war French era to Dien Bien Phu and the Geneva Convention.<br><br>
We also will commemorate the memory of A. Peter Dewey (OSS Mission in Saigon), who was killed by Vietminh troops who mistook him for a Frenchman. Some consider Dewey to be the first casualty of the Vietnamese-American War.<br><br>
Tanker, what years did you serve???<br><br>
Regards and best wishes.
